name: Neotiger
description: In Asia, the tiger is the largest feline carnivore. It is he who is considered the king of beasts in the east, which means that he is a symbol of power and might. Even the hieroglyph "king" in Chinese writing is depicted in the form of three stripes, like on a tiger's forehead. In ancient times, even before the era of agriculture, the tiger was the main totem animal.
